               <p>ALEXANDER BROWN. I am a <rs id="t18310106-109-viclabel628" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-109-victim1000 t18310106-109-viclabel628"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18310106-109-crimeloc629">Myddleton-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-109-crimeloc629" type="placeName" value="Myddleton-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-109-crimeloc629" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-109-off626 t18310106-109-crimeloc629"></join>. On the 22nd of December I lost a plaid cloak, which had been on a line inside my door - I was at home, but did not see it taken; a lad saw it taken - I went out, and saw the prisoner crossing the road, with it over his arm; I pursued him some distance - a gentleman stopped him, and gave him to me; I saw him drop the cloak.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-109-person1001">
